  "description": [
    "Burleson Disentangles Him self at the Eleventh Hour POSTMASTER G ENEE A L BURLESONS eleventh hour dropping of the telegraph wires on the eve of the voted strike of the telegraph and telephone workers over the United States has resulted in perhaps as great an amount of criticism as his retention of them The expected has happened in an unexpected manner remarks The Philadelphia Inquirer which paper goes on to observe In a supplementary statement Mr Burleson assures Congress that he has not really dropped the wires Oh dear me no He simply dissolves the operating board appointed by him in 1918 and directs that the systems again be operated by the regular operating officials under government supervi sion In other words he has ceased operating the wires but the govern ment has not abandoned responsibility and cannot until Congress acts Mr Burlesons statements and counter statements are a bit confusing but it is clear that he has done something and that something is to release his hold on the wires The Postmaster General seems to have been just as much of a success in handling the telegraph companies as Mr McAdoo was with the railroads just that much and"
  ],
